The paper deals with stable matching problems, which are a classic topic in computer science and artificial intelligence. The use of types to describe agents' preferences suggests a focus on algorithmic techniques for solving these problems, which would place the paper in the cs.AI and cs.DS categories. The paper also discusses the parameterised complexity of the problem, which suggests a connection to the cs.GT and cs.SI categories.
